Thanks Colin and Ken for your replies.

I&#39;d prefer to work in Java (as i&#39;m much more familiar with it) so i
downloaded JNeat and had a poke around. I&#39;ve ended up re-organising things a
bit and started getting my head around how it works. I&#39;ll check out
SharpNEAT but it would certainly benefit me to have a Java version so i&#39;ll
try and make the time to finish of the JNeat refactor and make it available.

Thanks again.

T

